1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,337
<i>Matmat had a breakdown</i>
<i>recalling of his accident at the river.</i>

2
00:00:05,255 --> 00:00:07,465
<i>But why do I feel like it's my fault?</i>

3
00:00:07,549 --> 00:00:11,886
<i>Talk to your siblings.</i>
<i>So they can finally come home.</i>

4
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:15,515
<i>Is it true his brother</i>
<i>wanted him dead before?</i>

5
00:00:15,598 --> 00:00:18,143
<i>- Stop gossiping!</i>
<i>- Stop it!</i>

6
00:00:18,226 --> 00:00:19,602
<i>You don't know him!</i>

7
00:00:19,686 --> 00:00:22,313
<i>It seems it was just</i>
<i>a simple fight with his brother.</i>

8
00:00:22,397 --> 00:00:25,316
<i>Don't underestimate</i>
<i>a simple misunderstanding.</i>

9
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:31,740
<i>A simple misunderstanding</i>
<i>could cost someone their life.</i>

10
00:00:31,823 --> 00:00:34,409
<i>Bro, take a look at your palm.</i>

11
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:37,787
<i>It might just remind you</i>
<i>why you shouldn't be with Mia.</i>

12
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:40,623
<i>I was just a dream. But I'm awake now.</i>

13
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:42,083
<i>I'm back to reality now.</i>

14
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:49,340
[theme music playing]

15
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:44,813
- [phone trilling]
- [quirky music playing]

16
00:01:47,732 --> 00:01:48,900
Talk to me.

17
00:01:48,983 --> 00:01:51,861
[inhales, exhales heavily]

18
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:54,572
You can't just ignore me.

19
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:58,660
[trilling continues]

20
00:02:00,662 --> 00:02:01,663
[sighs sharply]

21
00:02:01,746 --> 00:02:02,872
[phone clatters]

22
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:07,794
[quirky music continues]

23
00:02:14,717 --> 00:02:15,718
[scoffs softly]

24
00:02:22,058 --> 00:02:24,018
[quirky music ends]

25
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:29,440
[foreboding music playing]

26
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:30,525
[door opens]

27
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:33,528
- [playful music sting]
- [foreboding music ends]

28
00:02:33,611 --> 00:02:34,654
[blows]

29
00:02:34,737 --> 00:02:36,114
Matmat?

30
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:40,118
[blowing]

31
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:44,414
[chuckling]

32
00:02:44,497 --> 00:02:45,832
Oh, no.

33
00:02:45,915 --> 00:02:48,126
I think Matmat is asleep.

34
00:02:48,209 --> 00:02:51,754
How will he eat
the chicken barbecue I brought?

35
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:53,756
- [playful music playing]
- [blows]

36
00:02:55,884 --> 00:02:58,011
- [Jason chuckles]
- [sniffs]

37
00:02:58,094 --> 00:03:00,179
What a shame!

38
00:03:00,263 --> 00:03:05,560
It smells so good.
I cooked it myself at my restaurant.

39
00:03:05,643 --> 00:03:09,772
I even brought hot
soup that Mama Li cooked.

40
00:03:10,189 --> 00:03:13,109
Oh, wow!

41
00:03:13,192 --> 00:03:16,779
Well, I guess I should just go.

42
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:19,324
I need to go back to my restaurant.

43
00:03:19,407 --> 00:03:25,705
What shall I do with these?
Who will eat the barbecue and

44
00:03:25,788 --> 00:03:27,749
Mama Li's hot soup?

45
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:30,460
What do I do? Hmm…

46
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:32,211
What do I do?

47
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:35,465
I'll just leave
it here on the brown table.

48
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:36,841
Right next to Matmat.

49
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:38,176
Alright.

50
00:03:38,259 --> 00:03:39,427
I'll be off now.

51
00:03:39,510 --> 00:03:42,889
- [footsteps receding]
- [playful music continues]

52
00:03:42,972 --> 00:03:45,058
[door opens, closes]

53
00:03:50,813 --> 00:03:52,774
[playful music fades]

54
00:03:58,821 --> 00:04:02,909
Thank you, Mama Li and Jason.

55
00:04:04,953 --> 00:04:06,329
[knocking]

56
00:04:09,457 --> 00:04:10,792
- [knocking continues]
- Hmm?

57
00:04:15,296 --> 00:04:17,173
[hesitates] Jason?

58
00:04:20,843 --> 00:04:25,974
[unsettling music playing]

59
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:30,353
[whimpers] Jason's not here?

60
00:04:35,149 --> 00:04:41,656
[unsettling music continues]

61
