[foreboding music intensifies]

76
00:07:12,306 --> 00:07:16,269
[foreboding music crescendos]

77
00:07:17,937 --> 00:07:20,314
[birds chirping]

78
00:07:22,358 --> 00:07:23,359
Patrick?

79
00:07:28,489 --> 00:07:31,117
How were you able
to change clothes without coming home?

80
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:33,744
What about your undergarments?

81
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:35,746
[sorrowful music playing]

82
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:36,873
[Mia sighs sharply]

83
00:07:37,874 --> 00:07:38,875
Here.

84
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:40,626
I bought it for you.

85
00:07:41,085 --> 00:07:42,253
It's your size.

86
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:44,714
I checked your things at home to be sure.

87
00:07:45,506 --> 00:07:47,216
It's big…

88
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,551
Mia!

89
00:07:48,634 --> 00:07:50,178
The closet's big.

90
00:07:54,015 --> 00:07:55,600
Can we talk now?

91
00:07:56,392 --> 00:07:57,685
I'm still working.

92
00:07:57,768 --> 00:08:00,980
I didn't call you yesterday because
you said you were taking care of Matmat.

93
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:05,359
Now that you're not
busy with him, can we talk?

94
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:08,696
[birds chirping]

95
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:12,700
Fine. Let's talk.

96
00:08:18,831 --> 00:08:20,124
- Here, hold this.
- Okay.

97
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:22,043
That's Patrick's.

98
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:23,503
Don't touch it.

99
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:25,421
[Patty] Okay.

100
00:08:26,255 --> 00:08:27,340
[Pogi] Okay.

101
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:31,344
Hey! Didn't she just say not to touch it?

102
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,597
She knows Patrick's size?

103
00:08:35,556 --> 00:08:37,475
That's how close they are?

104
00:08:37,558 --> 00:08:38,768
I told you.

105
00:08:38,851 --> 00:08:40,144
I told you they're together.

106
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:42,355
Tsk! Give me that!

107
00:08:42,438 --> 00:08:43,606
[Mia] Patrick.

108
00:08:44,148 --> 00:08:45,733
Are you mad at me,

109
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:49,487
because you didn't tell
Matmat the truth about of our trip?

110
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:51,239
I'm not mad.

111
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:53,157
Then why aren't you talking to me?

112
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:57,411
Matmat is all I have time
to worry about right now.

113
00:08:57,495 --> 00:08:59,080
About your past?

114
00:08:59,163 --> 00:09:01,958
Because he recalled
how you wanted him dead?

115
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:03,834
That's not your fault.

116
00:09:05,253 --> 00:09:07,255
- You're only saying that because--
- No.

117
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:10,258
I know it's not your fault.

118
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:13,594
Because I saw everything.

119
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:15,888
- I was there.
- [melancholic music playing]

120
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:17,682
You didn't push him.

121
00:09:17,765 --> 00:09:20,476
It was an accident,
him falling into the river

122
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:22,311
[scoffs]

123
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:25,398
I even wished you'd let him drown.

124
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:29,485
But you were a poor little boy,

125
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:31,571
who loved his brother.

126
00:09:32,655 --> 00:09:34,156
You saved him.

127
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,242
[melancholic music continues]

128
00:09:36,325 --> 00:09:37,618
I know that.

129
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:40,079
But it doesn't mean
my conscience is clear

130
00:09:40,162 --> 00:09:41,831
- about what happened.
- [Mia huffs]

131
00:09:41,914 --> 00:09:43,040
There you go again.

132
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:47,753
Stop playing hostage
and victim to your family.

133
00:09:48,462 --> 00:09:50,172
You didn't commit a murder.

134
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:53,509
It's not your fault
your brother fell into the river.

135
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:56,053
[melancholic music continues]

136
00:09:56,137 --> 00:09:57,722
[scoffs] See?

137
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:02,143
I can be the key
to break all of your chains.

138
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:05,062
Come with me.

139
00:10:06,939 --> 00:10:08,316
Live with me.

140
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:11,902
[melancholic music continues]

141
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:13,863
I can't, Mia.

142
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:15,906
Come on, Patrick.

143
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:20,578
Even after Matmat admitted
he's been holding a grudge against you,

144
00:10:20,661 --> 00:10:22,788
do you think he still want to be with you?

145
00:10:24,999 --> 00:10:26,876
I can't go with you, Mia.

146
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:28,961
[melancholic music continues]

147
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:30,379
I don't believe you.

148
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:33,841
What you say is
different from what I see.

149
00:10:33,924 --> 00:10:36,052
Mia, don't twist my words!

150
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:38,262
I'm only saying what I see!

151
00:10:39,347 --> 00:10:41,766
That was just a dream, okay?

152
00:10:41,849 --> 00:10:43,601
Us swimming in the sea,
that night we spent together,

153
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:46,145
everything we shared that morning,
all of that was just a dream!

154
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:49,315
Are you hallucinating?

155
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,902
We were really together in Montanesa!

156
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:55,571
Yes.

157
00:10:55,988 --> 00:10:57,406
And now it's just a memory.

158
00:10:58,407 --> 00:10:59,659
- That's all it'll ever be.
- [melancholic music ends]

159
00:11:00,618 --> 00:11:02,411
Are you cutting me out of your life

160
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:04,830
just to try to make up for
your past with your brother?!

161
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:10,252
Mia, we were kids when he almost drowned.

162
00:11:10,336 --> 00:11:12,171
[somber music playing]

163
00:11:12,254 --> 00:11:14,215
I didn't know better then.

164
00:11:14,965 --> 00:11:16,759
I didn't realize I was hurting Matmat.

165
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:19,970
[somber music continues]

166
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:24,100
Now it's my fault…

167
00:11:27,061 --> 00:11:29,939
because when I'm with you,
it's like he doesn't exist.

168
00:11:30,022 --> 00:11:35,069
[somber music continues]

169
00:11:39,031 --> 00:11:41,325
It's wrong that I keep forgetting Matmat.

170
00:11:43,327 --> 00:11:46,956
It was a mistake that I ever entertained
having you in my life when we met again.

171
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:52,586
[somber music continues]

172
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:55,714
What about when you said
you were free because of me?

173
00:11:57,842 --> 00:11:59,135
Was that also a mistake?

174
00:12:04,890 --> 00:12:07,101
My reality is clearer to me now.

175
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:10,729
Stop lying.

176
00:12:12,064 --> 00:12:14,442
That's why Matmat calls you a liar.

177
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:15,693
That's the truth.

178
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:17,903
Enough.

179
00:12:20,072 --> 00:12:21,407
Patrick, please.

180
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:24,076
Enough.

181
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:26,328
Mia, let's end this.

182
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:29,623
[somber music continues]

183
00:12:29,707 --> 00:12:32,084
Stop holding on to what we had.

184
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:37,840
This is where it ends for us.

185
00:12:37,923 --> 00:12:41,177
- [Mia sniffles]
- [somber music continues]

186
00:12:42,344 --> 00:12:43,554
Patrick!

187
00:12:44,555 --> 00:12:45,931
Patrick, come back!

188
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:49,351
Patrick!

189
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:51,520
